    risks: ["VAR controversies could erode fan trust and dampen engagement", "Over-commercialization may alienate traditional football purists", "Security risks in host cities could disrupt matches and fan experiences"],
    opportunities: ["Emerging markets offer untapped potential for long-term fan growth", "Digital engagement platforms can monetize new audiences through NFTs and exclusive content", "Expansion to 48 teams creates new sponsorship and broadcasting opportunities"],
    outlook: "The next two weeks will be critical in determining the tournament’s legacy. Key storylines to watch:\n\n- **Group Stage Drama**: With 48 teams, the margin for error is slim. Expect more upsets as underdogs look to advance.\n- **VAR’s Future**: FIFA is under pressure to clarify VAR rules before the knockout rounds. A major refereeing blunder could spark a backlash.\n- **Commercial Momentum**: Brands will ramp up campaigns ahead of the semifinals, with a focus on fan engagement and experiential marketing.\n- **Emerging Markets**: Africa and Asia are driving viewership growth. Will this translate into long-term fan engagement for European clubs?\n\nThe knockout rounds could either cement this World Cup as a classic or expose its flaws. Either way, it’s already a game-changer.",
    conclusion: "The 2026 World Cup has reminded us why football is the world’s most beloved sport: it’s unpredictable, emotional, and full of surprises. Saudi Arabia’s win over Argentina wasn’t just a result—it was a cultural moment, proving that the old hierarchies of global football are crumbling. With record viewership, soaring sponsorships, and economic benefits rippling across host cities, this tournament is more than a sporting event; it’s a global phenomenon.\n\nBut challenges remain. VAR controversies threaten to overshadow the action, and the expanded format has raised questions about competitive balance. Yet, as the group stages draw to a close, one thing is clear: the World Cup is back—and it’s bigger, bolder, and more unpredictable than ever.",
